```

To verify a flaw with the sdk, I tried the same using Graph API Explorer Tool. Same problem there too. No data is being returned.

![](http://i.imgur.com/fNO29Wg.jpg)

How to go about this ?

Thank you.

---

update 0:

I posted the issue on a developer group on facebook and found that api was fine and so was the graph explorer tool. I created another campaign and checked for insights and it worked.

After going back to the docs again, I realised that I was missing the `date_preset` parameter.
On adding `date_preset`, the api started to five desired output.

This used to work, but stopped working with v1.1.3  A quick example:

```python
def adds_positional_arg_to_func(arg=1):
    def decorator(func):
        @wraps(func)
        def wrapper(*args, **kwargs):
            return func(arg, *args, **kwargs)
        return wrapper
    return decorator

@adds_positional_arg_to_func()
def logic(arg, param1, param2):
    """
    `arg` here is not a request parameter but is passed
    to the logic from the decorator.  When a route is sent to this
    logic function it will fail saying `arg` is a required request parameter.
    """
    return
```

This is due to the change made to the exec_params function to fix a different bug: https://github.com/upsight/doctor/commit/0952e1c0c463f709f1b11318dc7aed13f10e422c

