In gitlab by @sylvaingaudan on Aug 4, 2017, 09:14

Filter after=XXX produces a range query instead of a gte query:
```json
       { 
         "range" : { 
           "centerViewingDateTime" : { 
             "from" : XXX, 
             "to" : null, 
             "include_lower" : true, 
             "include_upper" : true, 
             "boost" : 1.0 
           } 
         } 
       } 
```
Filter before=YYY produces a range query instead of a lte query:
```json
      { 
         "range" : { 
           "centerViewingDateTime" : { 
             "from" : null, 
             "to" : YYY, 
             "include_lower" : true, 
             "include_upper" : true, 
             "boost" : 1.0 
           } 
         } 
       }, 
```

And a before=XXX&after=YYY filter produces a double range query instead of a single range query:
```json
"filter" : [ 
       { 
         "range" : { 
           "centerViewingDateTime" : { 
             "from" : null, 
             "to" : XXX, 
             "include_lower" : true, 
             "include_upper" : true, 
             "boost" : 1.0 
           } 
         } 
       }, 
       { 
         "range" : { 
           "centerViewingDateTime" : { 
             "from" : YYY, 
             "to" : null, 
             "include_lower" : true, 
             "include_upper" : true, 
             "boost" : 1.0 
           } 
         } 
       } 
     ]
```
